Yoshi Kuraishi<//username>
<date>1541511609720< /date>< Rating>
5<//Rating>
< review>
Tired of greasy Chinese food ? Try their sauteed Tao Myo (pea stem) in garlic sauce. I recommend this dish in March ~ May, due to the tenderness of this veggie. Try it, you will not be sorry ! It has a very delicate & light flavor. A satisfaction guaranteed ! Also, I like their pan fried rice vermicelli dish, Taiwanese cabbage with thick pieces of bacon, which goes well with pork belly over rice.< /review>

< text>
Love going to this place. The food is excellent. The dish I love the most is the fish in a broth of spicy soup with spinach.  Chicken in clay pot with basil and garlic sauce is a must try for those who likes to eat chicken. The drink of choice for me would be Taiwan beer. They have pork belly with garlic sauce as a appetizer. Every time I go there I would try something new. I would recommend this to anyone that wants to try Taiwanese cuisine.< /text>

< review>
A Taiwanese friend took us here and we had a delicious meal. My favorite dish was beef noodle soup. The rice and salt & pepper chicken were also delicious. The only thing I wasn't a big fan of was a plate with cold tofu, seaweed, and pig's ears. The people working there were very kind. There were only a few tables, though I wasn't clear if there was an upstairs also. I saw a staircase, but I don't know where it went.<//review>

<UserId.>112274749534477530569<//UserId.><Time>1349919706267<//Time>< pics>
None</pics>
< review>
It's funny what people like. One of my Chinese American friends found this place and loved it. Said he'd been looking for a place this good every since he moved away from L.A. But his friend, Taiwanese American who lives in L.A. says it's not so good. Not authentic. Another Taiwanese America friend in SF agrees.

As for me, I've been mostly happy. The sticky rice, the spicy wantons, the scallion pancakes, their tantan noodles, the pitan tofu, the sliced pork with garlic. I'm sure there is better in the bay area but I don't know better in the city. If there is tell me where and I'll go< /review>

<UserId.>101843888214781723641</UserId.>< review>
Absolutely wonderful experience where we scheduled a summer fun learning expedition high atop Mt Wilson touring the observatory that to this very day is currently employed by astronomers still researching the stars, planets & galaxies above! Lots of captivating history of this phenomenal place as our tour guide, Jed, offered extremely knowledgeable facts, dates, names figures of Mt Wilson and at the same time would tell stories of old making the tour all the more intriguing for us all. We "Highly" recommend Mt Wilson as an event you need to plan as unlike The Griffith Observatory, with all due respect is commercialized, Mt Wilson is truly an observatory that is real & in operation today used by scientist from around the world as well as USC & UCLA Colleges. During the 1pm 2 hr tour we got to see many of the telescopes & was allowed in the 100 ft. tower where a "100 Ton" telescope is still currently in use. There is also in theory the "Worlds Largest" Telescope on site! There are wonderful hiking trails close by & picnic areas if you wish to have lunch with the family or caf√© with basic food & drinks to quench your appetite. The aprox 5700ft elevation offers spectacular views of the city below on one side & Pacifico Mtn, and the 10,000ft San Antonio Mtn. on the other side! This trip/tour is fun for families, couples, singles, adventurists, outdoor enthusiast, hikers, bikers, walkers etc. Do check out the online website for more detailed information however there is no phone # to call for personal q & a.
High elevation provides slightly cooler weather up there & very nice breeze at times makes it very pleasant even during a heat spell when we went. We loved this trip & are planning to make this an annual event for the family!<//review>

<text>Mount Wilson has an elevation of 5,710 feet and is home to the Mount Wilson Observatory and also the home of an antenna farm known as radio row.  These antennas are used for broadcasting radio and TV signals to the greater Los Angeles area.  Mount Wilson also boasts its own Post Office.  You can find the small facility at 23 Video Road.  The antennas hum with electricity and have the ability to raise the hair on your head.  The views from Mount Wilson are spectacular on a clear day.  At the top you may be able to see the Channel Islands, San Clemente Island.  The horizon that you see over the ocean is actually 92 miles in the distance.</text><gmapID>0x80c2dd7871e3babb:0x94e3545e7f721aff< /gmapID>< time>

<user_id>105000259884509648991< /user_id>< user_name>
Witty Designer<//user_name>
<time>1620141207446</time><Rating>1<//Rating><Text>In the summer of 2019 my A/C unit failed. Climate Care was one of the bidders with whom I consulted. They were not the low bid but because of the rapport I developed with Chris (no longer with the company apparently) I chose Climate Care for the job. This job was completed to my satisfaction for the most part. I had some additional cleanup work to do after the installation team left. Not a big deal.
At the time, I wanted to add a whole house fan but finances dictated otherwise. Moving on to the summer of 2020, I contacted Chris about adding the whole house fan. Again, Climate Care was not the low bidder but I chose them for the job. This time, however, my level of satisfaction with the job is essentially nil. The unit is much louder than I anticipated, but since I don't run it for long periods of time, I can live with it. Not a big deal.
Now comes the major issues... There was some minor damage done to the ceiling near the install site. The location of the damage is in a most difficult spot to access otherwise it would be pretty easy for a pro to repair. One of the techs offered to change out the return air filters for the HVAC system, which I appreciated. Unfortunately, the tech bent up the return air framework in the process. Now that needs to be replaced. I brought this up with Climate Care after the install. I was told it would be taken care of. Not long after the install, the HVAC system quit working completely. I called Climate Care about that issue and a tech was dispatched to check it out. The tech's diagnoses was that there was no AC power going to the HVAC unit. I brought in an electrician to find the root cause. He found that a wire nut, that was used to daisy-chain power to the whole house fan was incorrectly sized and improperly installed causing an arcing condition between conductors in the wire nut. The arcing caused enough heat to melt and burn the wire nut. (This could have resulted in a fire!) Fortunately, the arcing was short-lived and the wire nut self-extinguished. The electrician repaired that connection and restored power to the HVAC unit.
I have made REPEATED calls to Climate Care to fix the damage that was done to the ceiling. Only once was a tech sent to inspect the damage. He said, "That's going to be hard to fix in that location." (Yeah, no kidding!) Again, I've called and called and called. ZERO response is what I've received. I just get told, "Someone will get back to you." It has been nearly 11 months now. I think that's been more than enough time to resolve this. I have come to the conclusion that Climate Care couldn't "CARE" less. It appears that I will have to hire someone to fix the damage on my own. I'm not sure if I can get reimbursed through small claims court or whatever I need to do. It shouldn't have come to this point. It did. I've run out of patience.

Bottom line? I would highly recommend finding another company to fill your HVAC needs. Climate Care does not back up their work/workmanship!<//Text>< Pictures>
None<//Pictures>

<rating>5< /rating>< Review>
Give this place a shot, great team!  While I was there, Larry, Medy and Laura were extremely friendly, helpful and professional.  I had 4 years worth of taxes that I needed help filing.  I had a bunch of questions about my situation and what I could count as a deduction.  Medy listened to my scenario and gave me her feedback, then followed up with some quick research and quoted me the answer.  Which confirmed her initial response in more detail.  I absolutely appreciate that level of dedication.  It reassured me that I was in good hands and I feel relieved that paperwork will be clean and worry free. Thank you Larry and Medy! I cannot thank you enough! Larry I am extremely grateful for the assistance in getting my tax issues resolved - all of it!

I would suggest making an appointment to ensure you have a quick visit. I was fortunate to arrive during a slow period. It's located right next to Smart and Final, making it very easy to find.  The parking lot does have traffic, but I always manage to find several open spaces.  On a side note, they also have snacks and beverages... it's a little thing, but it's an indication that they put forth a legitimate effort to try to ensure you have a pleasant experience with them.  They'll most likely provide you with flyer of other services that they provide (bookkeeping, accounting, copying, etc.).  They may apply to you and your state of affairs; me, not so much.  I'm sure that you'll receive a copy when you stop by.</Review>

< Text>
The Experience wasn't so bad as waiting for a table when you could see 15 to 20 of them outside nobody sitting at them. Then I asked for the heater to be turned on and it took five times before someone finally did. The young man who did turn the heater on was amazing and continue to come back and asked us if we needed anything. We ordered our orders first or appetizers I should say they were delicious we were very happy with what we got. However we then ordered the steak and bread because the orders had filled us up so much. It was ordered medium rare and we got it extra well done. Since I absolutely cannot enjoy anything that is that well-cooked I let them know told them I was kind of in a hurry because we have another place to go to they told me they could remake it in about 8 minutes. We waited and unfortunately this time it came back a little bit medium and instead of saying anything I just paid for our meal and I gave it to my dogs. It was rather tough. When the staff would spot us and see that I was trying to get their attention they were very responsive which was nice like I say the young man I believe his name was Jacob was extremely on it. Picking up dishes that were empty glasses that were empty asking if I want it more coffee excetera. So there were enough waitresses to handle the outside area it just seemed like it took a while to get them back to the table. This is a rough time for everybody so I would actually have give this three and a half Stars.</Text>

<review>Update... Still love it here!!!
Party of 3, sat at the bar. Place seems extremely loud but it's a bar. Waitress was great with her service. We ordered drinks and apps. <Rate>5</Rate>< review>
I was very impressed  by  the  way  that  this place was set up to accommodate diners during this difficult  time. I realize that they have mor space them some  other restaurants,  But they did make the outdoor area very comfortable,  there was even a TV. As for the food it was excellent and very plentiful.  My prime rib sandwich was loaded with meat and my friend's  steak house cobb was beautifully  prepared and it appeared freshly made. Our waitress Denise was very prompt  with our order and you could tell that she took pride in doing  her job. We went to a local restaurant  recently  were we had to ask for everything .  I want to support our local businesses during these times but sometimes  have not received  such a great service as we did here.< /review>

< rating>
5< /rating>
< Review>
Just went there yesterday, June 21st 2019 and our experience was fantastic. Our server was very polite and attentive yet gave his privacy and left us alone most of the time. When I asked another employee if he would change out our soup which was too salty for the clam chowder, he was very courteous and immediately brought us back a different type of soup that was more suitable for our taste. I also asked this other employee if he could bring us some extra bread and without hesitation brought us another basket of bread.
This is the type of service that will not break the bank of any restaurant yet goes a tremendously long way. Amazing that some places don't practice by this type of standard. But this restaurant Cool Hand Luke knows how to treat its customers hands down.
I'm generally not a big tipper, but our waitress earned her almost $10 tip by giving us an overall great experience for a lunch while we were out of town on vacation returning home.
I would definitely visit again when traveling through Santa Maria in the future<//Review>

James J. Griffin< /user_name>
<Review>We have dinner at Cool Hand Luke's almost every time I visit my Grandpa. I really like the old west vibe they have going on. It's a rather spacious restaurant so there's rarely a time they can't immediately accommodate a party of four. More than that and you should make a reservation, but the back room easily handled our party of fifteen.

The food is hearty. I had a 9oz New York strip last night and it was seasoned to perfection. I had a side of mashed potatoes which left the plate looking a little colorless, but that's my fault. I should have gone with the mixed veggies.

Their drink menu is eclectic and has quite a few strong mixed punches for the connoisseur of brightly colored sweet cocktails that will knock you on your ass. Think long island but blue, pink or whatever.

The tap list is pretty good and the happy hour bar is welcoming. Getting across College Ave is a bit of a pain during rush hour if you're coming from the 101 south, but other than that there's not any logistical issues.< /Review><user>106801717568154343538< /user>< response>
None</response>

I ordered to petite bacon-wrapped filets, medium rare. They came out to me medium well. They brought me to new steaks which tasted bland and they had a gray pallor.and one of the steaks, I found a rather large wooden skewer that was broken off in the steak, I was lucky I didn't bite into it. The whiskey peppercorn sauce that was supposed to come with the steaks, had more of a consistency of a lumpy gravy and tasted only of salt. The bloomin Onion that we ordered as an appetizer, was lukewarm to say the least and not crunchy at all. We also noticed, that the appetizer came out very quickly, as if it had already been made and was sitting there on a counter somewhere in the kitchen. The coffee that my friend ordered was bitter and I could tell that it was old coffee. Don't waste your time or money coming to this place. Well Cool hand Luke's in Santa Maria used to be very good, it has definitely gone downhill.< /Review>

<name>Jared Foster</name><Date>1478753161264</Date>< rate>
4< /rate>
< Review>
Would have given it 4.5 stars if I could. I had the Whiskey Skillet steak with Bleu cheese added and a side of calamari and beef stew. The steak and stew were absolutely excellent; the calamari very good. The steak was ordered medium rare, but was cooked slightly closer to medium. Still excellent. Calamari was a tad on the chewy side, but definitely better than most. The whiskey sauce was served on the side as it should be, not on the steak and it was delicious. Service was prompt and attentive, but not overbearing. All in all, I give the steak a recommended must have, and the calamari recommended.</Review>

None< /Resp>

<Text>Only average overall. Ordered Lukes western ribeye with the green beans and salad. Asked for medium rare, came medium well, very little pink at all. Somewhat tough and grissely on the cut.
The sauteed nushrooms and roasted garlic were excellent but not enough so to make up for the steak I only ate 1/2 of. Green beans side was also excellent, possibly sauteed in the mushroom butter. And the salad was only average, with watered down bleu cheese dressing.
Service was acceptable but not extra attentive, and since when does a restaurant not provide silverware by default? We had to ask for every piece of silverware individually.

<Review>We've been here three times and have left very satisfied after all three meals. Yes, it IS pricier than McDonald's or In & Out Burger, and that is because this is a top-notch steakhouse. Your steak is cooked to order, your fish is perfectly flaked, your calimari isn't too chewy or underdone. The lettuce in the salad could be fresher, but because of the amount that they serve daily, that would be impossible--they have to use bagged lettuce, like most every other restaurant. The beans you get to start your meal are hot and seasoned perfectly, as is your steak, chicken or fish, or even your burger (if that's how you roll.) We have not made it to dessert, not because it probably isn't great, like everything else, but just because we don't have room for it. We don't drink alcohol, but the tea is always fresh and the Coke is never flat or too carbonated. Hands down, my favorite place to eat a T-bone in central California.<//Review><pictures>None<//pictures><response>None< /response><GmapID>0x80ec6c95c9a5f0f1:0x1120ddd35e4cdeff</GmapID></record>
